      "content": {
        "title": "Shoulder Stiffness and Capsular Disorders — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Limited glenohumeral motion from adhesive capsulitis, postoperative or post-traumatic stiffness, and calcific tendinopathy.",
        "summary": "Adhesive capsulitis progresses through freezing and thawing phases. Manipulation under anesthesia and capsular release are options for refractory stiffness."
      },
